        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Apple Worldwide Developers Conference (WWDC)'); ?>
        <p>The <strong>Apple Worldwide Developers Conference (WWDC)</strong>, is a conference held annually in California by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Apple Inc', 'C'); ?>. The conference is used by Apple to showcase its new software and technologies for software developers. Attendees can participate in hands-on labs with Apple engineers, as well as in-depth sessions that cover a wide variety of topics. Until 2007, the number of attendees varied between 2,000 and 4,200; however, during WWDC 2007, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Steve Jobs', 'P'); ?> noted that there were more than 5,000 attendees. The WWDC events held from 2008 to 2015 were capped, and sold out at 5,000 attendees (5,200 including special attendees).</p>
